WEBVTT

1
00:00:09.570 --> 00:00:16.290
NOVEMBER 6. 1983
HAWKINS. INDIANA

2
00:00:27.130 --> 00:00:32.050
HAWKINS NATIONAL LABORATORY
US DEPARTMENT OF ENERGY

3
00:01:44.330 --> 00:01:45.460
Something is coming.

4
00:01:46.420 --> 00:01:48.090
It thirsts for blood.

5
00:01:48.170 --> 00:01:50.340
A shadow grows from the wall behind you.

6
00:01:50.720 --> 00:01:52.130
swallowing you up in the darkness.

7
00:01:52.840 --> 00:01:54.800
- It's almost here.
- What is it?

8
00:01:54.890 --> 00:01:56.220
What if it's a Demogorgon?

9
00:01:56.310 --> 00:01:57.930
We just need a bag.

10
00:01:58.020 --> 00:01:59.350
if it's a Demogorgon.

11
00:01:59.430 --> 00:02:00.480
This is not Demogorgon.

12
00:02:00.560 --> 00:02:02.810
The troglodyte army is attacking the cave!

13
00:02:02.900 --> 00:02:04.520
- Troglodytes?
- I told you.

14
00:02:08.530 --> 00:02:09.440
Wait.

15
00:02:10.530 --> 00:02:11.360
Did you hear that?

16
00:02:12.570 --> 00:02:14.030
This sound?

17
00:02:18.700 --> 00:02:20.580
It's definitely not troglodytes.

18
00:02:20.660 --> 00:02:22.250
No. it's something else.

19
00:02:24.790 --> 00:02:26.790
- Demogorgon!
- Oh. shit!

20
00:02:26.880 --> 00:02:28.340
- Oh. shit!
- Will. your move!

21
00:02:28.420 --> 00:02:29.710
- I don't know!
- Fireball!

22
00:02:29.800 --> 00:02:32.510
- We need 13 or more!
- This is a risk. Put up a defense.

23
00:02:32.590 --> 00:02:33.630
Don't be a pussy!

24
00:02:33.720 --> 00:02:35.640
- Throw the Fireball!
- Set up the Defense.

25
00:02:35.720 --> 00:02:38.430
Demogorgon is tired
of stupid human quarrels!

26
00:02:39.010 --> 00:02:41.390
- He's coming toward you.
- Throw the Fireball at him!

27
00:02:41.480 --> 00:02:43.770
- One more step!
- Set the Defense.

28
00:02:43.850 --> 00:02:44.690
He is furious!

29
00:02:46.770 --> 00:02:48.150
A ball of fire!

30
00:02:48.230 --> 00:02:49.980
- Shit!
- Where did he go?

31
00:02:50.070 --> 00:02:51.780
- Where is he?
- I don't know!

32
00:02:51.860 --> 00:02:53.490
- Did you get 13?
- I don't know!

33
00:02:53.570 --> 00:02:54.660
- Where is he?
- Oh. my God!

34
00:02:54.740 --> 00:02:56.320
- Mike!
- Oh. my God!

35
00:02:56.410 --> 00:02:57.490
Have you found it yet?

36
00:02:57.570 --> 00:02:59.120
- No. I can't find it!
- Mike!

37
00:02:59.200 --> 00:03:02.290
- Oh. my God!
- Mom. we're in the middle of a game!

38
00:03:02.370 --> 00:03:04.500
Game over. It's already 15 in the eighth.

39
00:03:04.580 --> 00:03:07.790
- Oh. my God! Fucking idiot!
- Why do we have to go?

40
00:03:07.880 --> 00:03:10.550
- Mom. just 20 more minutes!
- You have school tomorrow.

41
00:03:10.630 --> 00:03:13.090
It's time for Holly to invest. You can finish it over the weekend.

42
00:03:13.170 --> 00:03:14.090
But we're going to get lost!

43
00:03:14.170 --> 00:03:15.880
- Michael.
- I'm serious. mom.

44
00:03:15.970 --> 00:03:17.890
We have been planning this fight for two weeks!

45
00:03:18.680 --> 00:03:20.600
Who knew it would take ten hours?

46
00:03:20.680 --> 00:03:22.470
Have you been playing for ten hours?

47
00:03:23.930 --> 00:03:25.480
Dad. it's only 20 minutes...

48
00:03:25.560 --> 00:03:27.690
Listen to your mom.

49
00:03:29.520 --> 00:03:31.360
Damned piece of iron!

50
00:03:33.240 --> 00:03:34.240
Found it!

51
00:03:34.320 --> 00:03:36.110
- Does seven count?
- Did you get a seven?

52
00:03:36.820 --> 00:03:39.320
Did Mike see it? Then it doesn't count.

53
00:03:44.040 --> 00:03:45.210
Guys.

54
00:03:45.290 --> 00:03:47.040
- Does anyone want a piece?
- No.

55
00:03:50.630 --> 00:03:51.590
Yes.

56
00:03:52.590 --> 00:03:54.260
No. I don't think so...

57
00:03:55.340 --> 00:03:56.880
Yes. he is cute.

58
00:03:57.510 --> 00:04:00.300
No. Barb. I don't think so.

59
00:04:00.390 --> 00:04:01.760
- Barb.
- Hi. Nancy.

60
00:04:02.720 --> 00:04:05.730
There's a piece left if you want it.
Sausages and pepperoni.

61
00:04:05.810 --> 00:04:06.640
Wait.

62
00:04:13.900 --> 00:04:15.610
Something is wrong with your sister.

63
00:04:15.900 --> 00:04:17.240
What are you talking about?

64
00:04:17.320 --> 00:04:18.660
Everyone turns their nose up at him.

65
00:04:18.740 --> 00:04:21.740
Yeah. ever since
since I got involved with Steve Harrington.

66
00:04:21.830 --> 00:04:23.620
Yes. she turned into a fool.

67
00:04:23.700 --> 00:04:25.000
She has always been a fool.

68
00:04:25.080 --> 00:04:26.620
No. she was great.

69
00:04:26.960 --> 00:04:29.460
She played an elf in one of our campaigns.

70
00:04:29.540 --> 00:04:30.710
Four years ago!

71
00:04:30.790 --> 00:04:32.500
- I just remembered.
- See you later.

72
00:04:33.750 --> 00:04:34.590
A seven came up.

73
00:04:35.920 --> 00:04:37.670
A seven came up on the die.

74
00:04:38.800 --> 00:04:40.470
The demogorgon caught me.

75
00:04:42.640 --> 00:04:43.850
See you tomorrow.

76
00:04:59.660 --> 00:05:02.490
- Good night. ladies.
- Give your mom a kiss for me.

77
00:05:04.200 --> 00:05:06.200
Whoever beats me gets a comic book.

78
00:05:06.290 --> 00:05:07.830
- Any of them?
- Yes.

79
00:05:08.830 --> 00:05:11.040
Hey! Hey!

80
00:05:11.380 --> 00:05:13.250
I hadn't said it yet: "March!"

81
00:05:15.000 --> 00:05:16.460
Come back!

82
00:05:17.670 --> 00:05:19.260
I'm going to kill you!

83
00:05:19.340 --> 00:05:21.840
I'm picking up X-Men issue #134!

84
00:05:28.100 --> 00:05:29.230
Son of a bitch!

85
00:05:40.490 --> 00:05:43.700
HAWKINS NATIONAL LABORATORY
US DEPARTMENT OF ENERGY

86
00:06:28.700 --> 00:06:29.540
Mom?

87
00:06:30.250 --> 00:06:31.080
Jonathan?

88
00:06:31.710 --> 00:06:32.620
Mom?

89
00:06:54.560 --> 00:06:56.440
Hello? Hello?

90
00:08:25.860 --> 00:08:27.950
NETFLIX ORIGINAL SERIES

91
00:09:30.220 --> 00:09:32.430
...and that's all the news for this morning.

92
00:09:32.510 --> 00:09:33.850
Thank you for being with us.

93
00:09:33.930 --> 00:09:36.430
Now Liz will talk about local news.

94
00:09:36.520 --> 00:09:37.640
Thank you. Donna.

95
00:09:37.720 --> 00:09:38.850
So. local news.

96
00:09:38.930 --> 00:09:42.400
We were bombarded with reports
about power outages in the neighborhood.

97
00:09:42.480 --> 00:09:45.480
Yesterday. hundreds of Hawkins homes
lost power yesterday.

98
00:09:45.570 --> 00:09:47.820
Many people were left without electricity.

99
00:09:47.900 --> 00:09:49.990
The reason for the outages is still unclear.

100
00:09:50.070 --> 00:09:53.870
The spokesman for the Water and Electricity Service
of Roan County assured.

101
00:09:53.950 --> 00:09:57.700
that the power supply will be fully restored

102
00:09:57.790 --> 00:09:59.290
in the next few hours.

103
00:10:54.050 --> 00:10:55.890
HAWKINS POLICE CHIEF

104
00:10:58.720 --> 00:11:01.850
Other news.
Stay home or take an umbrella.

105
00:11:01.930 --> 00:11:04.520
The details will be told by
Charles. the weather forecast presenter.

106
00:11:09.070 --> 00:11:10.610
Where the hell are they?

107
00:11:11.110 --> 00:11:13.530
- Jonathan?
- Look at the couch!

108
00:11:13.610 --> 00:11:14.490
I've already watched it.

109
00:11:17.320 --> 00:11:18.330
Found it!

110
00:11:19.450 --> 00:11:21.790
Honey... I'll see you tonight.

111
00:11:21.870 --> 00:11:23.830
- Yeah. see you later.
- Where's Will?

112
00:11:23.910 --> 00:11:26.040
I haven't woken him up yet. He's probably still sleeping.

113
00:11:26.120 --> 00:11:29.290
- You were supposed to wake him up!
- Mom. I'm making breakfast.

114
00:11:29.380 --> 00:11:31.210
I told you a thousand times!

115
00:11:31.300 --> 00:11:34.590
Will. honey... it's time to get up.

116
00:11:38.300 --> 00:11:40.060
Did he come home yesterday?

117
00:11:40.390 --> 00:11:41.560
Is he not in the room?

118
00:11:41.640 --> 00:11:44.060
- Did he come home or not?
- I don't know.

119
00:11:44.140 --> 00:11:45.390
You don't know?

120
00:11:45.480 --> 00:11:48.650
- No. I came back late. I was at work.
- You were at work?

121
00:11:48.730 --> 00:11:52.190
Eric asked me to take over. I agreed to do it.
After all. we could use the money.

122
00:11:52.280 --> 00:11:54.490
- Jonathan. we've talked about this before.
- I know.

123
00:11:54.570 --> 00:11:56.990
You don't have to work.
when I'm on the night shift.

124
00:11:57.070 --> 00:11:59.820
It's nothing.
He was at the Wheeler's all day.

125
00:11:59.910 --> 00:12:02.080
- He must have spent the night there.
- No way.

126
00:12:02.160 --> 00:12:04.450
Sometimes I just can't believe my own ears!

127
00:12:10.040 --> 00:12:11.210
It's disgusting.

128
00:12:11.290 --> 00:12:13.510
- Mind your own business!
- Hello?

129
00:12:13.590 --> 00:12:15.340
Hi. Karen. It's Joyce.

130
00:12:15.420 --> 00:12:17.470
- Hi. Joyce.
- Mike. what the--?

131
00:12:17.550 --> 00:12:18.720
- Hey!
- Quiet!

132
00:12:18.800 --> 00:12:20.510
- Shut up.
- Are you kidding me?

133
00:12:20.600 --> 00:12:21.970
Is that Will screaming over there?

134
00:12:22.060 --> 00:12:23.560
Will? No. it's Mike.

135
00:12:23.640 --> 00:12:25.060
Will didn't spend the night with you?

136
00:12:25.140 --> 00:12:27.560
No. he left after eight o'clock.

137
00:12:28.140 --> 00:12:32.860
- Why? Is he not at home?
- He must have left for school early.

138
00:12:32.940 --> 00:12:34.940
- Thank you very much. Bye.
- You're welcome. Bye.

139
00:12:48.830 --> 00:12:52.840
HAWKINS HIGH SCHOOL
BUS STOP LOCATION

140
00:12:56.920 --> 00:12:57.760
It's strange.

141
00:12:58.840 --> 00:12:59.840
I don't see him.

142
00:12:59.930 --> 00:13:01.550
I'm telling you. his mom is right.

143
00:13:01.640 --> 00:13:03.350
He just left for school early.

144
00:13:03.430 --> 00:13:05.970
He is afraid that Gursky will take the test again.

145
00:13:06.060 --> 00:13:07.890
Here you go. ladies and gentlemen.

146
00:13:08.810 --> 00:13:11.310
Get your tickets to the freak show.

147
00:13:11.900 --> 00:13:13.940
Who will earn the most in the show?

148
00:13:15.780 --> 00:13:16.690
A little coal...

149
00:13:17.530 --> 00:13:19.610
Frog or Toothless?

150
00:13:23.490 --> 00:13:24.740
I'm betting on Bezuboy.

151
00:13:25.330 --> 00:13:28.710
I've told you a million times.
my teeth are growing.

152
00:13:28.790 --> 00:13:30.670
I have clavicular-cranial dysplasia.

153
00:13:30.750 --> 00:13:32.880
"I told you a million times!"

154
00:13:33.960 --> 00:13:34.790
Crunch your hands.

155
00:13:35.670 --> 00:13:36.920
Come on. you freak!

156
00:13:42.840 --> 00:13:45.510
God. it makes me twitch every time.

157
00:13:47.390 --> 00:13:49.430
- What assholes!
- It's even cool.

158
00:13:49.770 --> 00:13:51.810
It's like you have a superpower.

159
00:13:51.900 --> 00:13:53.560
Like Mr. Fantastic.

160
00:13:53.980 --> 00:13:55.940
But you can't fight evil that way.

161
00:13:56.320 --> 00:13:58.440
HAWKINS HIGH SCHOOL

162
00:14:04.570 --> 00:14:06.450
So. did he call?

163
00:14:06.530 --> 00:14:08.830
Don't yell.

164
00:14:09.160 --> 00:14:10.250
Did he call?

165
00:14:10.750 --> 00:14:12.500
I'm telling you. it's not like that.

166
00:14:13.250 --> 00:14:16.920
I mean. he likes me.
but not in that way.

167
00:14:18.130 --> 00:14:18.960
We just...

168
00:14:20.050 --> 00:14:21.550
We kissed several times.

169
00:14:21.630 --> 00:14:24.590
"We just... kissed a few times!"

170
00:14:25.090 --> 00:14:28.600
Nance. seriously. are you
you're gonna freeze to death right now?

171
00:14:28.680 --> 00:14:30.100
Of course not.

172
00:14:30.180 --> 00:14:32.480
You'd better be friends with me.

173
00:14:34.020 --> 00:14:36.730
Because you're going to get in touch with Tommy and Carol...

174
00:14:36.820 --> 00:14:38.190
What a disgusting thing!

175
00:14:38.270 --> 00:14:40.280
It was a one-time date.

176
00:14:41.190 --> 00:14:43.110
Or two.

177
00:14:46.450 --> 00:14:48.030
I'LL MEET YOU IN THE RESTROOM. STEVE

178
00:14:48.120 --> 00:14:49.330
What were you saying?

179
00:15:00.050 --> 00:15:00.880
Steve.

180
00:15:01.300 --> 00:15:02.840
- I have to go.
- Just a minute.

181
00:15:04.550 --> 00:15:06.390
Steve. I really...

182
00:15:06.850 --> 00:15:08.720
Seriously. I have to go.

183
00:15:08.810 --> 00:15:11.640
Wait.
Let's meet tonight.

184
00:15:13.140 --> 00:15:15.140
I can't. I have to study for the test.

185
00:15:15.230 --> 00:15:17.480
Stop it. Your GPA? 3.999...

186
00:15:17.560 --> 00:15:19.270
Kaminsky has very difficult tests.

187
00:15:19.360 --> 00:15:20.570
Then I will help you.

188
00:15:20.650 --> 00:15:22.780
- You failed chemistry.
- I got a C-minus.

189
00:15:22.860 --> 00:15:26.030
- That's another matter!
- I'll be at your place around eight.

190
00:15:26.110 --> 00:15:28.200
Are you crazy? Mom never...

191
00:15:28.280 --> 00:15:31.330
I'll climb in through the window without her seeing me.
I am an invisible ninja.

192
00:15:31.410 --> 00:15:32.660
You're crazy.

193
00:15:32.750 --> 00:15:35.460
Hold on. Just...
Okay. forget it. We could. uh.

194
00:15:36.040 --> 00:15:38.000
We... could sit in my car.

195
00:15:38.590 --> 00:15:40.750
Find a quiet place. park...

196
00:15:40.840 --> 00:15:41.800
Steve...

197
00:15:42.170 --> 00:15:44.130
I need to study.

198
00:15:44.470 --> 00:15:45.550
I'm not joking.

199
00:15:46.260 --> 00:15:48.390
That's why I'm going to choose a quiet place!

200
00:15:50.560 --> 00:15:52.430
Steve Harrington. you're an idiot.

201
00:15:58.270 --> 00:16:00.900
Meet me at the corner of Dearborn and Maple
at 8:00.

202
00:16:01.770 --> 00:16:02.980
Let's do some work.

203
00:16:08.870 --> 00:16:11.280
HAWKINS POLICE DEPARTMENT

204
00:16:11.370 --> 00:16:14.370
POLICE

205
00:16:16.370 --> 00:16:21.250
- It's great that you decided to come.
- Morning. Flo. Hey. everybody.

206
00:16:21.340 --> 00:16:25.260
- Hey. boss.
- Damn. you look good. boss!

207
00:16:25.340 --> 00:16:26.380
- Really?
- Yeah.

208
00:16:26.470 --> 00:16:29.180
Better than your wife's.
when I left her this morning.

209
00:16:30.010 --> 00:16:31.640
While you were sleeping or drinking.

210
00:16:31.720 --> 00:16:34.720
or whatever else you do on Monday mornings.

211
00:16:34.810 --> 00:16:35.850
Phil Larson called.

212
00:16:35.930 --> 00:16:38.350
Some children have stolen the gnomes again
from his garden again.

213
00:16:38.440 --> 00:16:40.060
Those garden gnomes again!

214
00:16:40.150 --> 00:16:41.980
I will get to it immediately.

215
00:16:42.480 --> 00:16:43.940
There are more pressing matters.

216
00:16:44.030 --> 00:16:46.650
Joyce Byers
didn't find her son at home today.

217
00:16:47.240 --> 00:16:48.660
I will also do this.

218
00:16:48.860 --> 00:16:51.280
- Give me a minute.
- Joyce is very upset.

219
00:16:51.370 --> 00:16:55.450
Flo. we've already discussed this.
Mornings are for coffee and reflection.

220
00:16:55.540 --> 00:16:59.620
- Chief. you have her now.
- Coffee and reflection. Flo!

221
00:17:08.010 --> 00:17:10.010
POLICE STATION
DISAPPEARANCE

222
00:17:10.090 --> 00:17:13.220
I waited an hour. Hopper!

223
00:17:13.300 --> 00:17:15.560
I apologize once again.

224
00:17:15.640 --> 00:17:17.020
I am losing my mind.

225
00:17:17.100 --> 00:17:20.690
Boys his age often have fun like this.

226
00:17:20.770 --> 00:17:22.730
Not my Will. He's not like that.

227
00:17:22.810 --> 00:17:24.400
- He would not have done that.
- Who knows?

228
00:17:24.480 --> 00:17:27.650
My mom thought I was at a debate.
but I was banging Chrissy Carpenter

229
00:17:27.740 --> 00:17:29.610
in the back seat of his father's car.

230
00:17:29.700 --> 00:17:32.660
He's not like you. Hopper.
He's not like me.

231
00:17:32.740 --> 00:17:35.240
Not like... the majority.

232
00:17:35.830 --> 00:17:39.210
He has a few friends.
But kids are so cruel.

233
00:17:39.290 --> 00:17:41.040
They mock him. They're teasing him.

234
00:17:41.120 --> 00:17:43.290
- They laugh at clothes...
- Clothes?

235
00:17:43.380 --> 00:17:45.290
- What's wrong with him?
- I don't know.

236
00:17:45.380 --> 00:17:47.670
- Does it matter?
- Maybe it does.

237
00:17:47.760 --> 00:17:48.800
Listen. he...

238
00:17:49.470 --> 00:17:50.800
a vulnerable child.

239
00:17:50.880 --> 00:17:54.720
Lonnie. Lonnie said he was weird.

240
00:17:54.800 --> 00:17:56.010
He called him a "faggot."

241
00:17:56.100 --> 00:17:57.890
- Is he one of them?
- He disappeared!

242
00:17:58.470 --> 00:17:59.480
That's what matters!

243
00:18:01.690 --> 00:18:03.900
When was the last time you were in touch with Lonnie?

244
00:18:06.860 --> 00:18:10.360
I heard he was in Indianapolis.
That was a year ago.

245
00:18:10.450 --> 00:18:12.700
- He has nothing to do with this.
- Give me his number.

246
00:18:12.780 --> 00:18:15.160
He has nothing to do with it. Trust me.

247
00:18:15.240 --> 00:18:18.290
Joyce.
in 99 out of 100 cases of missing children.

248
00:18:18.370 --> 00:18:20.660
They are found at a parent or relative's house.

249
00:18:20.750 --> 00:18:22.250
And in one case?

250
00:18:22.830 --> 00:18:25.710
- What?
- You said: "99 times out of 100."

251
00:18:25.790 --> 00:18:27.800
- And in that one case?
- Joyce.

252
00:18:27.880 --> 00:18:29.010
In one case?

253
00:18:29.090 --> 00:18:30.920
Joyce. this is Hawkins.

254
00:18:31.010 --> 00:18:32.760
Do you know what the worst case scenario is?

255
00:18:32.840 --> 00:18:35.140
happened here in four years?

256
00:18:35.220 --> 00:18:40.180
An owl attacked Elinor Gillespie.
because her hair looked like a hive.

