- No. No way.

523
00:38:28.620 --> 00:38:30.870
Stop it. You can't fail the test.

524
00:38:30.960 --> 00:38:32.750
You'll have to bear with me.

525
00:38:35.880 --> 00:38:36.710
What did I say?

526
00:38:38.340 --> 00:38:39.170
Ninja.

527
00:38:53.400 --> 00:38:54.770
You like ice cream. right?

528
00:38:56.110 --> 00:38:57.440
You look good with a smile.

529
00:38:58.360 --> 00:38:59.480
A smile. you know?

530
00:39:09.120 --> 00:39:10.700
Just sit quietly.

531
00:39:10.790 --> 00:39:13.420
I'll tell the person who came to leave. okay?

532
00:39:16.920 --> 00:39:17.960
Yes...

533
00:39:20.670 --> 00:39:22.670
- Good evening.
- Are you Benny Hammond?

534
00:39:22.760 --> 00:39:25.010
I'm afraid so. And I'm afraid we're closed.

535
00:39:25.090 --> 00:39:27.850
- Come back in the morning.
- Connie Frazier. Social Services.

536
00:39:27.930 --> 00:39:30.810
Social service? I'm sorry.
I didn't expect you so soon.

537
00:39:30.890 --> 00:39:33.310
- It's a long way to go.
- In the evening. the traffic is slow.

538
00:39:33.810 --> 00:39:36.060
I haven't told her you're coming yet.

539
00:39:36.150 --> 00:39:37.560
I didn't want her to run away.

540
00:39:38.190 --> 00:39:39.480
She is a little shy.

541
00:39:40.190 --> 00:39:42.440
- Like all the kids I work with.
- Yeah.

542
00:39:43.400 --> 00:39:44.780
And where is it?

543
00:39:45.160 --> 00:39:46.280
In the kitchen.

544
00:39:46.360 --> 00:39:48.120
- Come on. I'll introduce you.
- Thank you.

545
00:39:48.200 --> 00:39:50.660
- I'm sorry I wanted to expose you.
- No problem.

546
00:39:50.740 --> 00:39:52.910
Strange. On the phone. your voice

547
00:39:53.000 --> 00:39:54.290
sounded different...

548
00:40:24.490 --> 00:40:26.110
Shit. It's here.

549
00:40:36.210 --> 00:40:37.040
Hey!

550
00:40:37.420 --> 00:40:38.250
Can you feel it?

551
00:40:41.040 --> 00:40:42.710
- We'd better go back.
- No.

552
00:40:42.800 --> 00:40:45.090
We will not return. Don't go too far.

553
00:40:45.590 --> 00:40:46.420
Let's go.

554
00:40:47.840 --> 00:40:49.590
Do not switch from the sixth channel.

555
00:40:49.800 --> 00:40:51.010
And don't do anything stupid.

556
00:40:55.730 --> 00:40:57.020
Guys. wait!

557
00:40:57.730 --> 00:40:58.560
Wait!

558
00:41:05.440 --> 00:41:07.860
"What polymers are found in nature?"

559
00:41:09.110 --> 00:41:11.620
Starch and cellulose.

560
00:41:13.030 --> 00:41:18.460
"In CH4 molecules. the hydrogen atoms
are located at the tops..."

561
00:41:18.540 --> 00:41:19.460
Tetrahedrons.

562
00:41:19.960 --> 00:41:22.420
My God. how many cards have you made?

563
00:41:22.500 --> 00:41:24.170
You said you wanted to help.

564
00:41:25.550 --> 00:41:26.590
You know. let's do it this way.

565
00:41:26.670 --> 00:41:29.680
When you give the right answer.
I'll take off some of my clothes.

566
00:41:29.760 --> 00:41:32.430
- And every time you make a mistake...
- Pass.

567
00:41:32.510 --> 00:41:33.890
- Come on! Come on!
- No.

568
00:41:33.970 --> 00:41:35.140
- It'll be fun.
- No.

569
00:41:35.220 --> 00:41:39.520
"During fractional distillation
hydrocarbons are separated according to..."

570
00:41:39.600 --> 00:41:40.600
The melting point.

571
00:41:43.230 --> 00:41:44.320
The boiling point.

572
00:41:45.020 --> 00:41:47.650
- That's what I meant.
- But that's not what I said.

573
00:41:48.820 --> 00:41:50.740
- No.
- No?

574
00:41:51.490 --> 00:41:53.830
Do you... do you need help. or...

575
00:41:53.910 --> 00:41:54.740
No.

576
00:42:16.640 --> 00:42:19.140
- Steve. Steve. stop it.
- What?

577
00:42:19.230 --> 00:42:21.440
Are you crazy? My parents are here.

578
00:42:23.150 --> 00:42:25.570
It's strange. but I don't see them.

579
00:42:29.570 --> 00:42:31.150
Was that your plan?

580
00:42:32.070 --> 00:42:33.910
To get into my room...

581
00:42:34.200 --> 00:42:35.870
and win another victory?

582
00:42:35.950 --> 00:42:36.780
No. Nancy. No.

583
00:42:36.870 --> 00:42:40.580
- I am not Laurie. Amy. or Becky.
- You mean you're not a whore?

584
00:42:41.460 --> 00:42:42.620
That's not what I said.

585
00:42:42.710 --> 00:42:44.380
You're so cute when you lie.

586
00:42:44.960 --> 00:42:45.790
Shut up.

587
00:42:49.090 --> 00:42:50.420
Bad Steve.

588
00:42:51.380 --> 00:42:53.550
Bad. Stay away from Miss Nancy.

589
00:42:54.760 --> 00:42:56.600
You're an idiot. Steve Harrington.

590
00:42:57.560 --> 00:42:59.140
You are beautiful. Nancy Wheeler.

591
00:43:06.110 --> 00:43:08.690
"Compared to the speed of
of inorganic reactions

592
00:43:08.780 --> 00:43:12.490
the rate of organic reactions in general..."

593
00:43:15.490 --> 00:43:17.200
Oh. Jonathan!

594
00:43:17.530 --> 00:43:18.450
Did you do this?

595
00:43:19.240 --> 00:43:20.790
They are just great!

596
00:43:22.790 --> 00:43:24.000
It is true.

597
00:43:26.250 --> 00:43:28.750
I know I haven't given you enough time.

598
00:43:29.250 --> 00:43:30.840
I worked hard and...

599
00:43:31.630 --> 00:43:35.510
I am so sorry.
I hardly know how you live.

600
00:43:35.840 --> 00:43:37.600
And I am very sorry that this is the case.

601
00:43:42.060 --> 00:43:43.350
What is it?

602
00:43:44.310 --> 00:43:45.400
What is it. dear?

603
00:43:47.360 --> 00:43:49.360
- Nothing.
- Tell me.

604
00:43:49.440 --> 00:43:51.820
- Tell me. Come on. Can you...
- No.

605
00:43:52.280 --> 00:43:53.150
Just...

606
00:43:54.530 --> 00:43:56.240
I had to be here with him.

607
00:43:56.320 --> 00:43:59.330
No. Don't blame yourself.

608
00:43:59.410 --> 00:44:02.540
You are not guilty. Do you hear me?

609
00:44:02.620 --> 00:44:03.450
He...

610
00:44:03.960 --> 00:44:05.000
next door.

611
00:44:05.080 --> 00:44:06.330
I know that.

612
00:44:07.040 --> 00:44:08.920
I feel it in my heart.

613
00:44:10.300 --> 00:44:13.210
You have to... Just trust me on this.

614
00:44:16.130 --> 00:44:17.720
- Yeah.
- Look at this.

615
00:44:17.800 --> 00:44:20.180
Look at this. Look at these photos.

616
00:44:22.520 --> 00:44:24.640
- That's what we need. right?
- Yeah.

617
00:44:24.730 --> 00:44:26.350
Here. That's it.

618
00:44:30.440 --> 00:44:31.270
Hello?

619
00:44:33.150 --> 00:44:33.990
Hello?

620
00:44:35.070 --> 00:44:35.900
Lonnie?

621
00:44:35.990 --> 00:44:37.740
- Dad?
- Hopper?

622
00:44:38.320 --> 00:44:39.240
Who is this?

623
00:44:43.540 --> 00:44:44.700
Will?

624
00:44:45.160 --> 00:44:46.250
- Will?
- Is that Will?

625
00:44:49.540 --> 00:44:50.420
Mom. is that Will?

626
00:44:51.290 --> 00:44:52.380
Who is this?

627
00:44:52.880 --> 00:44:55.050
- What have you done with my boy?
- What? What?

628
00:44:55.130 --> 00:44:56.590
Give me back my son!

629
00:44:59.590 --> 00:45:01.640
Hello? Hello. who is this?

630
00:45:01.720 --> 00:45:02.560
Hello?

631
00:45:02.890 --> 00:45:03.850
Who is this?

632
00:45:04.680 --> 00:45:06.680
Mom. who was that? Who was that. Mom?

633
00:45:06.770 --> 00:45:08.850
- It was him.
- Look at me. Was that Will?

634
00:45:08.940 --> 00:45:10.150
- Yeah.
- What did he say?

635
00:45:10.230 --> 00:45:12.360
He was just breathing. He was just breathing.

636
00:45:12.440 --> 00:45:14.530
- Was there anyone else there?
- Я...

637
00:45:14.610 --> 00:45:17.110
- Mom. who was there? Who was it?
- It was him.

638
00:45:17.200 --> 00:45:20.490
I know it was his breath.
It was his breath!

639
00:45:21.280 --> 00:45:22.370
Will!

640
00:45:23.790 --> 00:45:26.120
- Will!
- Byers!

641
00:45:26.200 --> 00:45:28.920
I have your X-Men #134!

642
00:45:29.870 --> 00:45:31.830
Guys. I think we should go back.

643
00:45:32.040 --> 00:45:33.040
What's wrong. Dustin?

644
00:45:33.130 --> 00:45:35.380
If you are afraid. you can go home!

645
00:45:35.460 --> 00:45:37.300
I'm just being realistic. Lucas!

646
00:45:37.630 --> 00:45:39.340
No. you're just a coward!

647
00:45:40.300 --> 00:45:43.390
Maybe Will disappeared because he got into trouble.

648
00:45:43.470 --> 00:45:46.390
And we are in the same place.
where he was last seen!

649
00:45:46.470 --> 00:45:49.480
- We don't have any weapons on us!
- Dustin. shut up.

650
00:45:49.560 --> 00:45:52.650
- It's just... does that sound reasonable to you?
- Shut up. Shut up.

651
00:45:53.820 --> 00:45:54.650
Did you hear that?

652
00:46:17.920 --> 00:46:20.760
Translation of subtitles: Olga Chernyavska
